<ce:para>In this work, we present a superstructure based algorithm that combine the capabilities of modular process simulators - taking advantage of robust and rigorous simulation algorithms and properties estimations implemented in these simulators- and logic based Generalized Disjunctive Programming algorithms. The implementation is done in such a way that the NLPs with fixed topology are automatically set at the level of process simulator at each major iteration by the introduction of logical mixers and splitters. The non existing unit operations are then simply ignored at the NLP level and recovered in the Master problem formulation. The synthesis of a utility system is presented as a motivating example. The results show that the methodology is robust and reliable. Â© 2012 Elsevier B.V.</ce:para>
